        </item>
        <item>
            <title>一条蛇令日本新干线列车停驶，蛇缠绕高压电线引致停电</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2025/04/30/hebi-shinkansen/fun-tech/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=hebi-shinkansen</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2025/04/30/hebi-shinkansen/fun-tech/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Lawton]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Wed, 30 Apr 2025 15:49:26 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[科技新闻]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1305551</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>日本东海道新干线在 4 月 30 日傍晚突然出现供电异常，影响「新大阪－名古屋」及「新大阪－东京」两段列车运行，所幸在电力恢复及安全确认后约一小时内逐步回复正常。调查显示，事故源头竟是一条蛇爬上高压电线，导致短路，引发整段列车系统瘫痪。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430354screensh.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1305554" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430354screensh-694x390.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430354screensh-694x390.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430354screensh.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430214screensh.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1305555" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430214screensh-694x390.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430214screensh-694x390.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430214screensh.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>事故发生于当地时间下午 5 时 25 分左右，位于岐阜县内岐阜羽岛与米原站之间区间出现停电，直接令新干线主要路线运作受阻。根据 JR 东海透露，当时在大垣市静里町有蛇接触架空电缆，引发短路。由于事发地点是列车密集行驶路段，电力异常迫使多班列车紧急停驶。</p><p>在 JR 名古屋站，旅客面对突如其来的中断，纷纷涌向职员查询情况，不少乘客受困月台。虽然晚间 7 时已陆续恢复通车，但班次调动持续受影响，整体列车运作一度陷入混乱。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430454screensh.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1305556" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430454screensh-694x390.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430454screensh-694x390.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gw2025430454screensh.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>日本电视台报道指出，这次事故让人联想到新干线电力系统对外来生物干扰的脆弱性。尽管 JR 东海快速查明原因并迅速回复供电，但事件仍突显新干线网络在极端与偶发因素下的潜在风险。</p><div class="epyt-video-wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy"  style="display: block; margin: 0px auto;"  id="_ytid_99881"  width="590" height="332"  data-origwidth="590" data-origheight="332" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OchdVUDSalQ?enablejsapi=1&#038;autoplay=0&#038;cc_load_policy=0&#038;cc_lang_pref=&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;loop=0&#038;modestbranding=1&#038;rel=0&#038;fs=1&#038;playsinline=1&#038;autohide=1&#038;theme=light&#038;color=white&#038;controls=1&#038;" class="__youtube_prefs__  epyt-is-override  no-lazyload" title="YouTube player"  allow="fullscreen; accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen data-no-lazy="1" data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll=""></iframe></div><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2025/04/30/hebi-shinkansen/fun-tech/">一条蛇令日本新干线列车停驶，蛇缠绕高压电线引致停电</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
]]>
            </description>
